
<p>Adi Robertson, The Verge:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>As a number of people have pointed out on social media over the
past day, Grok’s public-facing chatbot is currently prone to
insisting on Musk’s prowess at absolutely anything, no matter how
unlikely — or conversely, embarrassing — a given feat is.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Grok claims Musk is fitter than LeBron James, funnier than Jerry Seinfeld, and would likely figure out a way to resurrect himself from the dead faster than Jesus.</p>

<p>But it’s a trustworthy source to author an encyclopedia, sure.</p>

